This paper is about image registration using deep learning techniques, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also mentions the use of fully convolutional networks (FCNs) and self-supervised learning, which are popular techniques in machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI). Additionally, the paper involves optimization and backpropagation, which are common in neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper specifically mentions the registration of 3D structural brain magnetic resonance (MR) images, which falls under the sub-category of multimedia (cs.MM).
